tions &amp; Archives documents the role that Brigham Young University-Idaho has played in the worldwide growth of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints and its relationship with the local pioneer community. The Permanent Library Holdings Policy describes the material we actively acquire in regards to campus history.</p>
<p><strong><a href="x51396.xml">Collection Development Policy:</a></strong> <img alt="McKay Library Circulation Desk 1970's" id="tileImage_80_0_0_480_388" src="http://contentdm.lib.byu.edu/utils/ajaxhelper/?CISOROOT=BYUICampus&amp;CISOPTR=586&amp;action=2&amp;DMSCALE=80&amp;DMWIDTH=480&amp;DMHEIGHT=388&amp;DMX=0&amp;DMY=0&amp;DMTEXT=services&amp;DMROTATE=0" style="float: right;" title="McKay Library Circulation Desk 1970's" width="250" /><br />The Collection Development Policy&nbsp;describes material we acquire and make available in the areas of local and church history, history of recordkeeping, and other areas of curricular and research interest.</p>
<p><a href="x47751.xml" title="Reading Room Rules"><strong>Reading Room Rules:</strong><br /></a>Our rules for using the Special Collections Reading Room, consisting of procedures, policies, and how to handle Special Collections materials.</p>
<p><a href="x51353.xml"><strong>Class Orientations:</strong> </a><br />Special Collections&nbsp;has obtained a variety of unique and interesting artifacts, books, and objects. Call us ahead and we can put together a presentation based around what you&nbsp;and your class are interested in seeing.</p>
<p><strong><a href="x50816.xml">Transferring Department Records:</a> </strong><br />Records Management provides information for transferring important, historical records to Special Collections and Archives, as well as general recordkeeping and retention guidelines for University Departments.</p>
<p><strong><a href="x48464.xml">Donations:</a></strong><br />How to donate&nbsp;materials to Special Collections.</p>
<p><strong><a href="x48460.xml" title="Copyright &amp; Use">Copyright &amp; Use:</a></strong><br />Information regarding the need to obtain copyright permission from the copyright holder as well as permission from Special Collections to use the materials.</p>]]></BodyCopy><xPower Type="GroupStart" GroupStart="" Name="PageComponents" label="Page Components" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" Expanded="true"><xPower Type="List" List="xpowercomponent_Optional" Name="OptionalColumnComponent" label="Optional Column Components" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" Component="" CompTypes="FacebookComponent;Image;ColumnTextComponent;Media;Quote" Expanded="false"><xPower Type="Component" Component="" Name="Optional" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" CompTypes="FacebookComponent;Image;ColumnTextComponent;Media;Quote" Expanded="false"/></xPower><xPower Type="Component" Component="x88894" Name="QuickLinksColumn1" label="QuickLinks Column 1" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" CompTypes="QuickLinksComponent" Expanded="false"/><xPower Type="Component" Component="x69384" Name="QuickLinksColumn2" label="QuickLinks Column 2" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" CompTypes="QuickLinksComponent" Expanded="false"/><xPower Type="Component" Component="" Name="QuickLinksColumn3" label="QuickLinks Column 3" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" CompTypes="QuickLinksComponent" Expanded="false"/></xPower><xPower Type="Component" Component="x51383" Name="HighlightedLinks" label="Highlighted Links" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" CompTypes="HighlightedLinksComponent" Expanded="false"/><xPower Type="Navigation" StartPage="x5" MaxDepth="" MaxNodes="" GenerationOrder="down" Navigation="Ancestors" Query="" Name="AncestorNavigation" label="Ancestor Navigation" readonly="true" hidden="true" required="false" Expanded="false"/><xPower Type="Component" Component="x47636" Name="SiteControl" label="Site Control" 